# UDS Figma Component Card

Specification for the canvas layout used on every component page in the UDS Components Figma file (and its testbed). One frame per component, named `udc-<id>-page`, holding seven cards in a fixed order. The component sets, sub-components, and instance previews live INSIDE these cards ÔÇö they are never loose top-level nodes.

## Why this rule exists

Component pages used to be a pile of unlabeled component sets sprawled at random positions. This rule defines the canonical "card" treatment so:
- Every page reads the same way (same card order, same eyebrows, same status colors)
- Future agents and skills produce identical output without re-deciding layout questions
- A designer can edit the visual template once and every agent run picks it up
- Token bindings are forced ÔÇö no raw hex anywhere

## File targets

- **Mainline:** `UDS Components` (file key `1XJoUJgtNpw4R0IIT3VjoK`) ÔÇö write only after explicit user approval
- **Testbed:** `UDS Components Testbed` / `UDS-Components-0.4-Testbed` (file key `HuQdX4txzccYX5GEnFnxAn`) ÔÇö safe to iterate

Always work on the testbed first unless the user explicitly says "mainline". Token bindings come from the `UDS Tokens` library (file key `iqKgR73ubUHpQTIcF7XGMy`); subscribe it to the file before binding anything.

## Page wrapper anatomy

```
udc-<id>-page (FRAME, 2800w, hug height, fill: surface-subtle)
Ôö£ÔöÇÔöÇ content (FRAME, FILL w, hug h, autolayout V, gap: space/1000, padding: space/800)
Ôöé   Ôö£ÔöÇÔöÇ HEADER          (dark card)
Ôöé   Ôö£ÔöÇÔöÇ ANATOMY         (light card)  ÔåÉ optional, omit for placeholder pages
Ôöé   Ôö£ÔöÇÔöÇ VARIANTS        (light card)  ÔåÉ omit if no inspectable component sets
Ôöé   Ôö£ÔöÇÔöÇ SUB-COMPONENTS  (light card)  ÔåÉ omit if no underscored components
Ôöé   Ôö£ÔöÇÔöÇ USAGE           (light card)
Ôöé   Ôö£ÔöÇÔöÇ ACCESSIBILITY   (light card)  ÔåÉ optional, requires accessibility.keyboard
